<section class="use-case-example">
  <div class="container container-narrow">
    <div class="use-case-content reveal">
      <h2>A Typical Conversation</h2>
      <div class="conversation-preview">
        <div class="conversation-bubble conversation-bubble--user">
          <p>I want to start meditating but I can never stick with it. I've tried like four times.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="conversation-bubble conversation-bubble--maya">
          <p>Four times means you really want this—that's a good sign. Let me ask: when you tried before, how long were you trying to meditate each session?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="conversation-bubble conversation-bubble--user">
          <p>Usually 10-15 minutes. The app I used had these guided sessions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="conversation-bubble conversation-bubble--maya">
          <p>Got it. Here's what I'd suggest: forget the app for now. Tomorrow morning, right after you sit down with your coffee, take three deep breaths. That's it. Three breaths. Can you do that?</p>
        </div>
        <div class="conversation-bubble conversation-bubble--user">
          <p>I mean... yeah, anyone can do that.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="conversation-bubble conversation-bubble--maya">
          <p>Exactly. That's the point. We're building the habit of pausing, not training for a meditation championship. Do three breaths for a week, then let's talk about what's next.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

